<p>The <a href="https://www.amacad.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">American Academy of Arts &amp; Sciences</a> has announced its new members for 2025, and several philosophers are among them.<span id="more-53600"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-45862 aligncenter wp-dark-mode-bg-image" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/american-academy-seal-cutout.png" sizes="auto, (max-width: 701px) 100vw, 701px" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/american-academy-seal-cutout.png 4639w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/american-academy-seal-cutout-300x200.png 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/american-academy-seal-cutout-1024x683.png 1024w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/american-academy-seal-cutout-768x513.png 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/american-academy-seal-cutout-1536x1025.png 1536w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/american-academy-seal-cutout-2048x1367.png 2048w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/american-academy-seal-cutout-400x267.png 400w" alt="" width="701" height="468" /></p>
<p>They are:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://philosophy.jhu.edu/directory/lucy-allais/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Lucy Allais</strong></a>,  Johns Hopkins University</li>
<li><a href="https://philosophy.wisc.edu/staff/brighouse-harry/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Harry Brighouse</strong></a>, University of Wisconsin-Madison</li>
<li><a href="https://www.gc.cuny.edu/people/noel-carroll" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Noël Carroll</strong></a>,  CUNY Graduate Center</li>
<li><a href="https://www.jenanni.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Jenann Ismael</strong></a>,  Johns Hopkins University</li>
<li><a href="https://philosophy.northwestern.edu/people/continuing-faculty/lackey-jennifer.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Jennifer Lackey</strong></a>,  Northwestern University</li>
<li><a href="https://www.oysteinlinnebo.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Øystein Linnebo</strong></a>,  University of Oslo (International Honorary Member)</li>
<li><a href="https://its.law.nyu.edu/facultyprofiles/index.cfm?fuseaction=profile.overview&amp;personid=20152" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Liam B. Murphy</strong></a>,  New York University School of Law</li>
<li><a href="https://www.petersinger.info/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Peter Singer</strong></a>,  Princeton University</li>
</ul>
<p>In an <a href="https://www.amacad.org/news/new-member-announcement-2025" target="_blank" rel="noopener">announcement</a>, the Academy&#8217;s president, Laurie Patton, said: &#8220;These new members’ accomplishments speak volumes about the human capacity for discovery, creativity, leadership, and persistence. They are a stellar testament to the power of knowledge to broaden our horizons and deepen our understanding.&#8221;</p>
<p>The full list of new members is <a href="https://www.amacad.org/new-members-2025" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
<p>The American Academy of Arts &amp; Sciences is a learned society founded in 1780 by John Adams, John Hancock, and other Founding Fathers of the United States. You can learn more about it <a href="https://www.amacad.org/about-academy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/04/23/philosophers-among-new-members-of-the-american-academy-of-arts-sciences/">Philosophers Among New Members of the American Academy of Arts & Sciences</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>